  "text": "Before commencing people tracking, background subtraction is employed to extract foreground regions. The background subtraction method used in our system is to some extent similar to the work by McKenna et al. [CITATION_1] . The difference is that while in [CITATION_2] RGB colour space was used, we use HSV colour space as it is well suited in segmenting chromatic and intensity information. We use a circular statistics method for computing the mean and variance of the hue component, described below.",
